to get ready with distance sensor code for the hc-sr04 module the dtc (device tree compiler) library needs to be installed:

    wget -c https://raw.githubusercontent.com/RobertCNelson/tools/master/pkgs/dtc.sh
    chmod +x dtc.sh
    ./dtc.sh

additionally the pasm compiler needs to be installed. It is currently not available in the debian repos a
manual installation has to be done:

    wget https://github.com/beagleboard/am335x_pru_package/archive/master.zip --no-check-certificate
    unzip masster.zip
//    mkdir /usr/include/pruss
    cd am335x_pru_package-master/pru_sw/app_loader/include/
    cp pruss_intc_mapping.h prussdrv.h /usr/include/
    cd ../interface/
    CROSS_COMPILE= make
    cd ../lib/
    cp libprussdrv.a libprussdrvd.a libprussdrv.so libprussdrvd.so /usr/lib/
    ldconfig??
    cd ../../utils/pasm_source/
    source linuxbuild 
    cp ../pasm /usr/bin/
    
// get capebone patch for the kernel
//    sudo apt-get install bc device-tree-compiler lzma lzop libncurses5-dev 
    
    

rebuild kernel (https://www.eewiki.net/display/linuxonarm/BeagleBone):
    git clone https://github.com/RobertCNelson/bb-kernel
Note add options "-c http.sslVerify=false" to all git clone calls, also in the scripts/git.sh file!
    cd bb-kernel/
    git checkout origin/am33x-v3.8 -b tmp
    ./build_kernel.sh
   
if git exits with "index-pack died of signal 9 git debian"
create a swap file:
    sudo dd if=/dev/zero of=/var/swapfile bs=1M count=128
    sudo mkswap /var/swapfile
    sudo swapon /var/swapfile
    sudo reboot
add swap to /etc/fstab
    sudo echo "/var/swapfile none swap sw 0 0" >> /etc/fstab
    sudo reboot
    
install the capebone dtc manager
    git clone -b 3.14-ti https://github.com/RobertCNelson/dtb-rebuilder.git
    cd dtb-rebuilder/
    make
    sudo make install
